# Integrate Jam Sessions Into Existing Piano/Drums UI

Instead of separate jam-piano/jam-drums pages, reuse the full existing UI (AR studio, camera, falling notes) with WebSocket broadcasting layered on top.

## Proposed Changes

### app.js — Jam Setup Redirect

After host/join + instrument selection, navigate to the **existing** pages:
- Piano → [initPianoComposer(); showPage('piano-composer');](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airjam-jam-export/airplay%202/app.js#1219-1244)
- Drums → [initDrumsComposer(); showPage('drums-composer');](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airplay%202/app.js#1921-1953)

Modify `pickPianoBtn` and `pickDrumsBtn` click handlers in [initJamSetup()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airjam-jam-export/airplay%202/app.js#1921-1994) (lines 2221-2248).

---

### app.js — Send Notes Over WebSocket

The existing `window.addEventListener('message')` handler (line 2113) already forwards notes to `jamSessionManager` when connected. For direct key clicks, add a global hook to [createPianoKeys()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airjam-jam-export/airplay%202/app.js#766-785) and drum pad click handlers that also calls `jamSessionManager.sendNote()` if connected.

---

### app.js — Receive Remote Notes  

Update `jamSessionManager.onRemoteNote` callback to:
- Call [playRemoteNoteSound()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airplay%202/app.js#347-376) (already exists) for audio
- Call `pianoNoteManager.triggerKeyPress()` for piano visual feedback on the existing UI
- Flash drum pads on the existing drums UI

---

### app.js — Jam Status Badge

When jam is active, inject a floating badge showing "Room: XXXXXX" + "Leave Jam" button into the current page header. Remove it in [exitJamSession()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airjam-jam-export/airplay%202/app.js#2022-2029).

---

### session_server.py — Player Join Notification

When a new player connects to a room, broadcast `{"type": "player_joined", "player_id": "..."}` to existing room members. Handle this in `JamSessionManager.onmessage` to show a toast.

---

### instruments.html — Toast Container

Add a simple `<div id="jam-toast">` for showing join notifications.

## Verification
- Host a session, pick Piano → should see the full existing piano UI with room badge
- Friend joins → host sees "Player joined!" toast
- Play keys on one side → sound + visual on both sides
